local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010790-300x225.jpg 300w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010790-768x577.jpg 768w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010790-1536x1153.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010790-2048x1538.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" style=\"padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)\">\n<p>The grimly lit stage of my photographic world that initially appears to inhibit ideas surprisingly outdoes itself. The lights have become the protagonists of the piece, rather than the supporting fixtures behind the viewer or hidden in the ceiling. The action is no longer a result of the cohesion between a set&#8217;s lights and camera, instead it is now a part of the process of creating a photograph. This is the uninspiring film industry motto &#8220;Lights, Action, Camera&#8221;, unmistakedly performed with a twist.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ultimately, the light shines in the darkness, but the darkness has not overcome it!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-dots\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>Let us close this thought with a shot as the camera puts itself to sleep.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignwide size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1922\" src=\"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2208\" srcset=\"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-scaled.jpg 2560w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-300x225.jpg 300w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-1024x769.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-768x577.jpg 768w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-1536x1153.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010244-2048x1538.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If you are viewing this on medium, I&#8217;d like to invite you to view this blog on my new website at yannichau.i234.me\/lights-camera-action\/. This is where this article is originally crafted, where images not only supplement the blog content, but also belong to it. The formatting on Medium no longer satisfies my eneds as a photograper [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":2205,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[2,5,1],"tags":[11,17],"class_list":["post-2177","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-blogs","category-photography","category-uncategorized","tag-hong-kong","tag-photography"],"acf":[],"featured_media_src_url":"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/1010270-1024x769.jpg","_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2177","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/yanni-test-local-wp-newdb.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2177"}],"version-history":[{"count":10,"